MAY 1
ST. JOSEPH THE WORKER
Feast
Office of March 19th , p.    except:

PRAYER:
O God, Creator of all things,
who laid down for the human race the law of work,
graciously grant
that by the example of Saint Joseph and under his patronage
we may complete the works you set us to do
and attain the rewards you promise.
Through our Lord Jesus Christ, your Son,
who lives and reigns with you in the unity of the Holy Spirit,
one God, for ever and ever.


INVITATORY
Come, let us worship Christ the Lord
who was honored to be known as the son of a carpenter, alleluia.

BENEDICTUS: Saint Joseph faithfully practiced the carpenterâ€™s trade. He
is a shining example for all workers, alleluia.

MAGNIFICAT: Christ the Lord felt honored to be known as the son of
a carpenter, alleluia.


